==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sprue
<hw>Sprue</hw> <pr>(spr⟦udd⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Etymol.
uncertain.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Founding)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>Strictly, the hole through which melted metal is poured into the
gate, and thence into the mold.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The waste piece
of metal cast in this hole; hence, dross.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Same as <er>Sprew</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sprug</ent>⟦br⟧
